<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

<!-- ===== EDIT PER POST: title / description / url / image / dates ===== -->
<title>POST TITLE — Your Blog</title>
<meta name="description" content="One-sentence summary of the post, 120–155 characters, with the main keyword near the front.">
<link rel="canonical" href="https://leeduri.github.io/aifinote/posts/POST-SLUG.html">

<meta property="og:type" content="article">
<meta property="og:title" content="POST TITLE">
<meta property="og:description" content="One-sentence summary of the post.">
<meta property="og:image" content="https://leeduri.github.io/aifinote/posts/images/POST-SLUG-cover.png">
<meta property="og:url" content="https://leeduri.github.io/aifinote/posts/POST-SLUG.html">
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">

<!-- Structured data: Article + Breadcrumb (the combo SEO/AEO actually rewards in 2026) -->
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "BlogPosting",
      "headline": "POST TITLE",
      "description": "One-sentence summary of the post.",
      "image": "https://leeduri.github.io/aifinote/posts/images/POST-SLUG-cover.png",
      "datePublished": "2026-07-19",
      "dateModified": "2026-07-19",
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Your Name" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Your Blog" },
      "mainEntityOfPage": "https://leeduri.github.io/aifinote/posts/POST-SLUG.html"
    },
    {
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://leeduri.github.io/aifinote/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "AI", "item": "https://leeduri.github.io/aifinote/?cat=ai" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "POST TITLE" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="../assets/style.css">
</head>
<body>

<header class="site-header">
  <div class="wrap-wide bar">
    <a class="brand" href="../index.html">Your Blog</a>
    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="../index.html">Home</a>
      <a href="../about.html">About</a>
    </nav>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="wrap">
  <nav class="breadcrumb">
    <a href="../index.html">Home</a> ›
    <a href="../index.html?cat=ai">AI</a> ›
    <span>Post title</span>
  </nav>

  <article>
    <span class="tag" data-cat="ai">AI</span>
    <!-- H1 = the post title. Put the main keyword near the front. -->
    <h1>Your Post Title Goes Here</h1>

    <div class="post-meta">
      <span>By <strong>Your Name</strong></span>
      <span>Jul 19, 2026</span>
      <span>6 min read</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Cover / representative image. 1200×630 recommended for social + Discover. -->
    <figure>
      <img class="cover" src="images/POST-SLUG-cover.png" alt="Descriptive alt text about what the cover shows">
      <figcaption>A short caption for the cover image.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <!-- Lead: state the conclusion / main idea in the first 2–3 sentences.
         No "In this post we will..." throat-clearing. -->
    <p>Open with the payoff. Tell the reader in the first two or three sentences
    exactly what they'll get and what you concluded — search engines and AI
    overviews read the intro to decide what this page is about.</p>

    <h2>First section heading</h2>
    <p>Keep paragraphs to 2–4 sentences. Break ideas up so the page scans well
    on a phone.</p>

    <p>Use <strong>bold</strong> for the key phrase in a paragraph, and link to a
    <a href="#">related post</a> when it helps the reader go deeper.</p>

    <h3>A question readers actually ask?</h3>
    <p>Answer it in one or two sentences right under the heading. This
    question-then-answer shape is what gets pulled into AI answers and featured
    snippets.</p>

    <!-- In-body image example -->
    <figure>
      <img src="images/POST-SLUG-1.png" alt="Describe the second image here">
      <figcaption>Optional caption.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>A section with a list</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Point one</strong> — a short explanation.</li>
      <li><strong>Point two</strong> — a short explanation.</li>
      <li><strong>Point three</strong> — a short explanation.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>A section with a table</h2>
    <div class="table-scroll">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Option</th><th>Best for</th><th>Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Option A</td><td>Beginners</td><td>Free</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Option B</td><td>Power users</td><td>$$</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <blockquote>
      <p>Use a blockquote to highlight a key takeaway or a quote.</p>
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Wrapping up</h2>
    <p>Close with a short summary and a next step — a link to a related post
    keeps readers on the site and helps SEO.</p>

    <!-- Author box -->
    <div class="author-box">
      <div class="avatar"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="name">Your Name</p>
        <p class="desc">One or two lines about who you are and why you write about
        AI, money, and everyday life.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Related posts (internal links = better SEO + longer sessions) -->
    <nav class="related">
      <h2>Related posts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#">Another post title →</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">And one more →</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <!-- ===== AD SLOT: paste guides/adsense-snippet.html contents here ===== -->
    <div class="ad-slot">
      <!-- Google AdSense code goes here, at the very end of the article body -->
    </div>
  </article>
</main>

<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="wrap-wide bar">
    <span>© 2026 Your Blog</span>
    <span><a href="../about.html">About</a> · <a href="https://github.com/leeduri">GitHub</a></span>
  </div>
</footer>
</body>
</html>
